      <item>
        <title>Running server 24/7 on Ubuntu vps?</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@moparisthebest Moparisthebest]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/u/moparisthebest">@moparisthebest</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>[quote=“lordman346, post:1, topic:309540”]I have setup my server on my vps and I can run it via a shell script with the following:</p>
<p><span class="bbcode-b">!<span class="hashtag">#bin</span>/bash<br>
cd &amp;&amp; cd noobscape &amp;&amp; java server</span></p>
<p>To run it 24/7 I need to turn that into a service.[/quote]</p>
<p>Turn that into a service?  That doesn’t even make sense.  All you need to do is add another command.</p>
<p><span class="bbcode-b">!<span class="hashtag">#bin</span>/bash<br>
cd &amp;&amp; cd noobscape &amp;&amp; nohup java server &amp;</span></p>
<p>nohup stands for no hangup, which means that when you log out, the process you started with nohup will not be stopped.  The &amp; at the end starts the process in the background so that you can execute other commands or type ‘exit’ to exit out of the terminal.</p>
<p>Alternatively, you can use a program called ‘screen’, but that is more complicated than nohup and &amp;.</p>
<p>Understand?</p>
          </blockquote>
          <p><a href="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/t/running-server-24-7-on-ubuntu-vps/309540/11">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
